Troops of the former Soviet Union were withdrawn from the Armenian enclave of  Nagoro-Karabakh yesterday after they were fired upon during clashes between Armenian  and Azerbaijani militants.
Armenians in the enclave want unification want with Armenia.
Government troops under fire along the Azerbaijani and Armenian border will also be  withdrawn.
The conflict has been going on four years, and now both sides are using  sophisticated weapons.
The Defense Minister of the Commonwealth of Independent  States has long said troops would not become casualties in ethnic conflicts in the former  Soviet Union. 
